#README
## function
*able to add the zöllner illusion to the game
*able to modify the parameters of the stripes to adjust the strength of the illusion.
	* parameter : length, density, width, angle
	* reference : Oyama, T. Determinants of the Zöllner illusion. Psychol. Res 37, 261–280 (1975). https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00309038 

## explain
### DemoScene
A zollnerpackage and a Sample Object is already in the scene. The Sample Object is used as the default target of the 'zollnerpackage'.
*What user can do in the 'zollnerpackage': 
	*change the target object 
	*modify the parameters
	*generate the stripes as the childobject to the duplicate target 

*What user can see
	*the immediate stripes demo 



### SampleGame
a demo game which can be added with the zöllner illusion
####step 1: 
create the object with zöllner illusion
*method 1 : create the object in the DemoScene
*method 2 : create the object in the SampleGame
	*drag the Asset/Scenes/Resources/zollnerpackage to the scene
	*select the object than drag it to the target field in the 'zollnerpackage'
	*modify the parameters and than press the 'generate' button

####step 2: 
drag the objects to the SampleGame/EventSystem/Ground Manager(Script) Target Field

#### Done

#### Notice
*window size:432*768

####### Bug
* the angle of the stripes generated by the package is inaccuracy . (a little difference to the )